
[1]abusive

   ABU'SIVE, a.

   1. Practicing abuse; offering harsh words, or ill treatment; as an
   abusive author; an abusive fellow.

   2. Containing abuse, or that is the instrument of abuse, as abusive
   words; rude; reproachful. In the sense of deceitful, as an abusive
   treaty. [Little used.]
